description: Planted along street side. Specimens just starting to flower - the leaves suggest strongly this is a hybrid with S. chathamica (note overlapping leaflets) but the dark green, glossy leaf surfaces, and smaller more open flowers are features of S. cassioides. I have seen similar hybrids sold in the garden trade often as S. tetraptera or S. macrocarpa. Its a real shame people are planting these thinking they are indigenous - S. cassioides has even appeared in some parts of Auckland as 'restoration' plantings... A real concern.

description:
Cultivated tree grown from seed collected from Motukaraka Point, Kawhia Harbour and planted into garden in 1996. I have kept first flowering records of this tree since 2010. Image of first flowers noted for this season (see phenology records at www.nzpcn.org.nz).

Over the last seven years in chronological order first flowering dates for this tree have been:

23 August 2010
1 September 2011
2 August 2012
14 August 2013
18 August 2014
25 August 2015
27 August 2016

See http://naturewatch.org.nz/observations/1889581

Planted specimens lining a pedestrian access from the Estuary bush and from the paved footpath on this side of Kaipatiki Road Extension.
